  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN162-kilavi">iravukkuṟikkaṇ talaimakaḷaik kaṇṇuṟṟu <app><lem>nīṅkun</lem><rdg wit="#RK">nīṅkiya</rdg></app> talaimakaṉ taṉ neñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to his heart when he left after having seen HER during the night tryst.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN162">
        <l><anchor n="1"/>koḷakkuṟai paṭā<supplied>a</supplied>k kōṭuvaḷar kuṭṭat</l>
        <l>taḷappari tākiya kuvaiyirun tōṉṟaṟ</l>
        <l>kaṭalkaṇ ṭaṉṉa māka vicumpi</l>
        <l>ṉaḻaṟkoṭi yaṉṉa miṉṉuvacipu nuṭaṅkak</l>
        <l>kaṭitiṭi yurumoṭu kataḻuṟai citaṟi</l>
        <l>viḷiviṭa ṉaṟiyā vāṉimiḻ naṭunā</l>
        <l>ḷaruṅkaṭik kāva<supplied>la</supplied> rikaḻpata ṉōkkip</l>
        <l>paṉimayaṅ kacaivaḷi yalaippat tantai</l>
        <l>neṭunaka roruciṟai niṉṟaṉa ṉāka</l>
        <l>vaṟaleṉa vavirvaruṅ kūntaṉ malareṉa</l>
        <l>vāṇmukat talamaru <supplied>mā</supplied>yitaḻ maḻaikkaṇ</l>
        <l>mukainirait taṉṉa māvīḻ veṇpa</l>
        <l>ṉakaimāṇ ṭilaṅku nalaṅkeḻu tuvarvāyk</l>
        <l>kōlamai viḻuttoṭi viḷaṅka vīcik</l>
        <l>kāluṟu taḷiri ṉaṭuṅki yāṉātu</l>
        <l>nōyacā vīṭa muyaṅkiṉaḷ vāymoḻi</l>
        <l>nallicai tarūu miravalark kuḷḷiya</l>
        <l>nacaipiḻaip paṟiyāk kaḻa<supplied>ṟo</supplied>ṭi yatakaṉ</l>
        <l>kōḷa<supplied>ṟa</supplied> vaṟiyāp payaṅkeḻu palaviṉ</l>
        <l>vēṅkaicēr veṟpakam pōntoṉ ṟaruvi<anchor n="2"/></l> <!-- line extensions of C7 and RK see in note  -->
        <l>nērko <supplied>ṇe</supplied>ṭuvaraik kavāaṟ</l>
        <l>cūrara makaḷiriṟ peṟaṟ<supplied>ka</supplied>ri yōḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>At midnight, clouds rumble without knowing a moment of interruption, (6)</l>
        <l>while flashes waver like sheets of fire (4)</l>
        <l>across the vast sky that is as if one saw the ocean (3)</l>
        <l>of dark appearance, in masses that are difficult to measure (2)</l>
        <l>in the conch-growing depth that does not suffer from want when [something] is taken, (1)</l>
        <l>scattering hasty drops along with fiercely roaring thunder, (5)</l>
        <l>when I looked for the moment of watchmen’s negligence in the protection difficult [to evade], (7)</l>
        <l>[and] stood on one side of [her] father’s tall mansion, (8d-9)</l>
        <l>while the moving wind suffused with chill dashed, (8a-c)</l>
        <l>she embraced [me], for the frailty of pain to be dispelled, (16a-c)</l>
        <l>unendingly, trembling like a sprout touched by the wind, (15)</l>
        <l>[her] tresses come to shine like black sand, [her] flower-like (10)</l>
        <l>rain eyes with choice lashes that flutter in [her] bright face, (11)</l>
        <l>[her] big desirable white teeth like buds put in a row, (12)</l>
        <l>[her] fine coral mouth that shines gloriously in a smile, (13)</l>
        <l>flinging [her arms] so that [her] beautiful, apt, excellent bracelets sparkle, (14)</l> 
        <l>– she who is as difficult to get as an awesome celestial damsel (22)</l>
        <l>from the slope of the beautiful(?) great mountain, (21)</l>
        <l>with waterfalls moving as one within the mountains grown with kino trees (20)</l> 
        <l>[and fruit-]yielding jackfruit trees that do not know of ceasing [to grow] bunches, (19)</l>
        <l>of Atakaṉ with anklets [and] bracelets who does not know failure in [his] affection, (18)</l>
        <l>who is remembered by(?) beggars who [in return] give [him] fame from [their] truthful mouths. (16df.)</l>
      </lg>
